Body: Description: We are receiving reports from numerous end users that when they click on "Deploy" for new flash drives, nothing happens. We also noticed that some workstations we were actually able to troubleshoot are showing a last check-in time that does not match with what the admin console is reporting.
Client left vm on a separate case. will respond via this case

What We've Learned Updated: Epp client is not communicating with the server.
Logs show timeout cURL error 28.

What We've Learned Updated: Epp client is not communicating with the server.
Logs show timeout cURL error 28.
Unable to ping the IP 160.87.0.221 mentioned by the customer.
Next Steps Updated: Reregistered the client and asked the customer to check.
Next Steps Updated: CHecking with devop regarding the 160.87.0.221 ip from the customer.

What We've Learned Updated: Epp client is not communicating with the server.
Logs show timeout cURL error 28.
Unable to ping the IP 160.87.0.221 mentioned by the customer.

We have whitelisted the 160.87.0.221 address on AWS, the clients are now communicating with the server.

There is still an issue with opening the EL app from the File Explorer, we asked on the solution-engineers teams chat and asked the customer to collect diagnostics from the computer this error reproduces.

Next Steps Updated: CHecking with devop regarding the 160.87.0.221 ip from the customer.

We are waiting for the customer to collect the log files, and for our engineers to get an answer on the teams chat.
